<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870127-0085 </DOCNO><HL> Joy Manufacturing TenderIs Extended Until Monday</HL><DD> 01/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> JOYTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)INDUSTRIAL EQUIPMENT, MACHINE TOOLS (IND) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Joy Acquisition Corp. and JMC Acquisition Corp. said they extended to Monday the expiration date, proration period and withdrawal rights of the $35-a-share offer for as much as 16.7 million Joy Manufacturing Co. common shares.    In December, Joy Manufacturing, a Pittsburgh-based maker of oil field and petroleum equipment and coal-mining machinery, agreed to go private in a leveraged buyout valued at $620 million.    As of early yesterday, 4.2 million shares had been tendered in the offering, excluding 2.1 million shares tendered pursuant to guarantees of delivery. The initial offer expired at 12:01 a.m today. </TEXT></DOC>